entry.def: If the amount or size of something swells or if something swells it, it becomes larger than it was before.

example.ex: The human population swelled, at least temporarily, as migrants moved south...
example.tran: 随着移居者南移,人口出现膨胀，至少是暂时性膨胀。

example.ex: By the end of this month the size of the mission is expected to swell to 280 people...
example.tran: 到这个月底，参加该任务的人员规模将有望增至 280 人。

entry.def: If something such as a part of your body swells, it becomes larger and rounder than normal.

example.ex: Do your ankles swell at night?...
The limbs swell to an enormous size.

entry.def: If you swell with a feeling, you are suddenly full of that feeling.

example.ex: She could see her two sons swell with pride.
example.tran: 她能看出她的两个儿子充满了骄傲。

entry.def: If sounds swell, they get louder.

example.tran: 不知从何处响起天籁般的音乐。

entry.def: A swell is the regular movement of waves up and down in the open sea.

example.ex: We bobbed gently up and down on the swell of the incoming tide.
example.tran: 我们随着涨潮的浪涌轻轻地起伏。

entry.tran: 极好的;了不起的;非常棒的
entry.def: You can describe something as swell if you think it is really nice.
